      <div class="featured-eyebrow">About</div>
      <h2>About the Summer School</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        The NetSec Early-Career Scholars Summer School (ECS³) aims to provide training and
        mentorship to Early-Career Researchers (ECR) in order to foster the next generation of
        European security scholars.
      </p>
      <p>
        It is organised jointly by the European Initiative for Security Studies (EISS) and
        Stockholm University, under the framework and financial support of the
        <a href="https://netsec-cost.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">COST Action NetSec</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The long-term ambition of the Summer School is to contribute to promoting academic
        excellence in Europe and to nurture the development of a new generation of scholars that
        engage on international &amp; European security issues with their counterparts across the
        globe. It is an excellent opportunity for early career researchers to receive feedback on
        their work, expand their networks, and engage with leading scholars in the field.
      </p>
      <p>
        The inaugural NetSec Summer School took place at Stockholm University from 9 to 11 June
        2026, in the lead-up to the <a href="/2026.html">European Security Studies Conference</a>.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5); display: flex; gap: var(--space-3); flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center;">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://netsec-cost.eu/summer-school.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{ icon("external-link") }} How to apply, on NetSec</a>
      </p>
      <p class="muted" style="font-size: var(--fs-sm); margin-top: var(--space-3);">
        Applications for the 2026 edition have closed. NetSec keeps the authoritative page for
        eligibility, financial support, the lecturer line-up and future calls.
      </p>
